A 
\emph on
vector space 
\emph default
is a non-empty set 
\emph on

\begin_inset Formula $V$
\end_inset

 
\emph default
over a field 
\begin_inset Formula $\mathbb{K}$
\end_inset

 together with two binary operations 
\begin_inset Formula $+:V\times V\to V$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\cdot:\mathbb{K}\times V\to V$
\end_inset

 , called 
\emph on
vector addition 
\emph default
and 
\emph on
